@startuml state-find
'' PlantUML over Mermaid because the find bar is a small finite-state machine with a count-parameterised
'' state and self-looping cycle transitions; PlantUML state diagrams give composite/parameterised states,
'' self-transitions, and per-state colour. Literal palette hexes: blue-violet #7590DB ephemeral :ui/find,
'' green #67B11D the "matches present" (painted) state, grey for hidden.
!include _vv-theme.iuml

title Find-bar state machine (:ui/find)\n{:visible? :query :count :idx}

skinparam state {
  BackgroundColor #7590DB
}

[*] --> Hidden

state "Hidden" as Hidden #DDDDDD : visible? = false\nhighlights cleared
state "Visible (empty)" as Empty #7590DB : visible? = true\nquery = ""  ·  count = 0
state "Visible (matches: n)" as Matches #67B11D : visible? = true\ncount = n > 0  ·  idx ∈ 1..n\nhighlights painted

Hidden  --> Empty   : Ctrl+F  /  [:find/toggle]
Empty   --> Hidden  : Ctrl+F (toggle off) | Escape\n/ [:find/close] → clear!

Empty   --> Matches : type query (matches found)\n[:find/set-query] → search! → count n>0
Empty   --> Empty   : type query (no match)\ncount = 0
Matches --> Empty   : edit query → 0 matches\nor clear the field
Matches --> Matches : type a new query\n(re-run search!, new n)

Matches --> Matches : Enter / ↓  [:find/cycle +1]\nidx ≔ (idx mod n)+1  (1-based)
Matches --> Matches : Shift+Enter / ↑  [:find/cycle -1]\nidx ≔ ((idx-2 mod n)+1)

Matches --> Hidden  : Escape / ×  [:find/close]\n→ clear! (delete vv-find, vv-find-current)
Matches --> Hidden  : Ctrl+F (toggle off)

note bottom of Matches #FFF6D6
  cycle! wraps with modular arithmetic:
  idx ≔ (idx + dir) mod n  (internally 0-based;
  returns the 1-based index shown as "idx/n").
end note

legend right
  |= Colour |= State / concept |
  |<#DDDDDD>| Hidden (find bar closed, highlights cleared) |
  |<#7590DB>| Visible, no current matches (app-db :ui/find) |
  |<#67B11D>| Visible with painted matches (CSS highlights) |
endlegend
@enduml
